<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "1C">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A1306011" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
HO2S-1 and HO2S-2 Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A1306010">HO2S-1 and HO2S-2 On-Vehicle Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306011001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Touching exhaust system components when they are still hot may cause burns.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Make sure the exhaust system has cooled down before removing the HO2S.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connector of HO2S-1 or HO2S-2 and release its wire harness from clamps.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Perform following steps before removing HO2S-1 or HO2S-2.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
For HO2S-1, remove exhaust manifold cover, if necessary. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1B06002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
For HO2S-2, hoist vehicle.
</ptxt>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove HO2S-1 (1) or HO2S-2 (2) from exhaust manifold or exhaust No.1 pipe.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B130006.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "65.001mm" ver = "01" gw = "205" gh = "168"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1306011002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
Reverse removal procedure noting the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten HO2S-1 (1) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1C005">
<t-part>
HO2S-1
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
45
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
4.6
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
33.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten HO2S-2 (2) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1C006">
<t-part>
HO2S-2
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
45
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
4.6
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
33.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B130007.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "65.001mm" ver = "01" gw = "222" gh = "168"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Install exhaust manifold cover, if removed. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1B06002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After installation, check exhaust leakage from sensor with engine running.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
